      </row>

      <row>
            <cell> </cell>
      </row>

      <row>
      </row>

      <row>
            <cell>1st choice</cell>
            <cell>B</cell>
            <cell>B</cell>
            <cell>C</cell>
            <cell>A</cell>
      </row>

      <row>
            <cell>2nd choice</cell>
            <cell>C</cell>
            <cell>C</cell>
            <cell>A</cell>
            <cell>D</cell>
      </row>

      <row>
            <cell>3rd choice</cell>
            <cell>D</cell>
            <cell>A</cell>
            <cell>D</cell>
            <cell>C</cell>
      </row>

      <row>
            <cell>4th choice</cell>
            <cell>A</cell>
            <cell>D</cell>
            <cell>B</cell>
            <cell>B</cell>
      </row>

      <row>
            <cell> </cell>
      </row>
</tabular>
            
      </introduction>
      <task>
            <statement>
                  <p>
                        The school board votes using a Borda count. 
              Which company will get the contract?
                  </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                  <p>
                       <m>\begin{array}{clcr}A &#x26; 5*1+3*2+3*3+1*4 &#x26;=&#x26; 24 \\ 
                              B &#x26; 5*4+3*4+3*1+1*1 &#x26;=&#x26; 36 \\ 
                              C &#x26; 5*3+3*3+3*4+1*2 &#x26;=&#x26; 38 \\ 
                              D &#x26; 5*2+3*1+3*2+1*3 &#x26;=&#x26; 22 \\\end{array}
                        </m>
                        so C wins
                  </p>
            </solution>
      </task>
      <task>
           <p> Does this seem fair?  Why or why not?</p>
            <solution>
            <p>No; two-thirds of the voters picked Bob's Builders as their first choice!</p>
      </solution>
</task>


